text: Lakly () is a rural locality (a selo) and the administrative center of Laklinsky Selsoviet, Salavatsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 925 as of 2010. There are 10 streets. == Geography == It is located 31 km from Maloyaz. == References == Category:Rural localities in Salavatsky District
title: Lakly
